                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Colonel
                            <persName type="to">Marshall S. Carter</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-24">24 July
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1173. Prefer to let bill expire with Congress as indicated last para your
                        95280<note n="51" xml:id="d426fn51">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> if that can be arranged. If deemed desirable, you are at liberty to
                    acquaint Sol Bloom with views in 1164.<note n="52" xml:id="d426fn52">Telegram of
                        July 22, <ref target="#pg_753">p. 753</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
